name: diethyl adipate

An example substance similar in structure, hexanedioic acid (adipic acid), has a melting point of 153°C, which is substantially higher due to the ability to hydrogen bond. The addition of two ethyl ester groups will considerably lower the melting point due to the loss of hydrogen bonding capability and addition of the ethyl groups that create a less rigid structure compared to a carboxylic acid. Taking into consideration these factors, we can apply the following adjustments: Long carbon chain: +20, Ether linkage (-OCO-): -40 each (x2), Ethyl groups: -5 each (x2).
